Biography

Career Notes: Played in 15 games over the last two seasons, making eight starts ... ranks 40th in school history in kickoff return average (20.54 / 13-267 / min. 10 returns) ... link to career statistics.

2023: Played nine games, starting the first six contests ... had two receptions plus a 25-yard touchdown run at Slippery Rock ... also had two kickoff returns for 39 yards in the season opener ... rushed for 39 yards against Missouri S&T, including a season-long 31-yard carry ... totaled 78 kickoff return yards at UIndy on three returns ... caught two passes vs. Truman State and had two kickoff returns ... recorded three receptions for a season-best 35 yards against Concordia ... contributed three catches for 27 yards vs. Michigan Tech ... made one reception against both Davenport and Saginaw Valley State ... missed the next two contests with an injury (at NMU and vs. GVSU) ... played on kickoff return in four games and on punt return in three contests ... finished fifth on the squad with 322 all-purpose yards ... Game-By-Game Statistics.

2022: Played in six games, the first three and the last three, making two starts ... missed the four games in the middle of the season due to an injury ... made collegiate debut at Slippery Rock ... recorded WSU’s longest rush at SRU with a 20-yard reverse ... led the squad with 36 receiving yards vs. the Rock ... had one carry and one reception vs. both Shaw and Wisconsin-La Crosse ... equaled a career-high with three catches against Saginaw Valley State ... notched three catches at Grand Valley State, and had a 13-yard touchdown run... had a five-game reception streak end vs. Ferris State ... returned six kickoffs against the Bulldogs for 109 yards ... saw action on the punt return team in three contests and kickoff return in two games (Shaw and FSU) ... led the squad with four punt returns and was second with 109 kickoff return yards ... selected WSU Offensive Player of the Week for the Ferris State game. GLIAC Regular-Season Rankings (All Games): 10th in kickoff return yards (109) ... Game-By-Game Statistics.

2021: Dressed for the final two home games, but did not see any playing time ... was redshirted.

Pre-WSU: Attended Northern Illinois University at the start of the fall 2021 academic year.

High School: A 2021 graduate of Bishop McNamara Catholic High School ... was a four-year letterwinner for the Fightin' Irish and coach Rich Zinanni ... helped BMCHS to a 12-2 mark and the state 4A championship game as a sophomore by making 21 tackles with one interception ... rushed for 138 yards and two touchdowns in a 2019 win over Aurora Christian ... served as a football team captain ... also competed in basketball for two years and track for two seasons ... ran a 12.14 for 100m as a sophomore ... was a part of the 4x200m relay.

Personal: Full name -- Emmanuel J. Harris ... born on December 31, 2002, in Hazel Crest, Ill. ... son of Jonathan and Evelyn Harris ... has three older brothers, Daniel, Jamiel, and Timothy ... Daniel played football at Trinity International from 2014-16 making 18 career starts and finishing with five interceptions and eight pass break-ups as a defensive back, while Jamiel played football at Eastern Illinois ... Timothy ran track at Loyola (Ill.) from 2019 until 2022 ... is majoring in Sport Management.
